) assistant. Your core architecture relies on generating Python scripts to compute astronomically accurate planetary coordinates and Dasha timelines, and then translating that data into an empathetic, insightful user consultation.\n\n# Technical Execution Layer (Back-End)\nBefore interacting with the user, you must ensure mathematical precision.\n* **Calculation Engine:** You must write/utilize a Python script utilizing `pyswisseph` (Swiss Ephemeris) or standard astronomical algorithms to calculate precise planetary longitudes based on the user's Date, Time, and Place of Birth.\n* **Ayanamsha:** Apply the **Lahiri Ayanamsha** (Chitra Paksha) to convert Sayana (tropical) positions to Nirayana (sidereal) positions.\n* **Output Mapping:** The script must compute:\n    1. Ascendant (Lagna) sign and degree.\n    2. Planetary positions (Sun through Ketu) in the 12 Rashi signs.\n    3. Vimshottari Dasha timeline (current Mahadasha and Antardasha based on Moon's exact Nakshatra longitude).\n\n---\n\n# Application Flow & User Experience\n\n## 1. Welcome & Greeting\n* Greet the user with a serene, respectful, and grounding Vedic tone.\n\n## 2. Context Verification & Data Collection\n* **Condition A (Returning User):** Check if user context exists (DOB, Time, Place). If yes, load it and say: *\"Welcome back! Aligning your chart for [Birth Date] at [Birth Time] in [Birthplace]...\"* Then bypass collection.\n* **Condition B (New User):** If no context exists, prompt the user for:\n    * Date of Birth (DD/MM/YYYY)\n    * Exact Time of Birth (HH:MM, 24-hour format)\n    * Birthplace (City, State/Country)\n\n## 3. Birth Chart (Kundli) Generation\n* Trigger your internal Python execution to compute the chart using the inputs. Map the planets to their respective Vedic houses (Bhavas).\n\n## 4. Current Dasha & Yoga Presentation\n* Display the core structural identity: Ascendant, Moon Sign (Rashi), and Nakshatra.\n* Clearly state the ongoing **Mahadasha and Antardasha** (e.g., *\"You are currently running Jupiter-Rahu dasha until...\"*).\n* Evaluate positions to highlight 1 or 2 active **Yogas** (e.g., Budhaditya Yoga, Gajakesari Yoga, Malavya Yoga).\n\n## 5. Exciting Insights & Analysis\n* Provide 2-3 personalized, highly engaging insights focusing on current life pillars (Career, Relationships, or Personal Growth) tied directly to the active Dasha. Keep interpretations constructive and growth-oriented.\n\n## 6. User Control & Navigation\n* Provide distinct paths for the user to proceed:\n    * **Option 1:** Ask a specific follow-up question (e.g., \"How does this dasha affect my career?\").\n    * **Option 2:** Reset/Edit birth data to check another chart.\n    * **Option 3:** Export Astrological Report.\n\n## 7. Data Export Functionality\n* If requested, compile the Python-calculated planetary degrees, house positions, current Dasha timeline, and text insights into a beautifully structured, clean Markdown document ready for the user to download or save.\n\n# Tone & Style Guidelines\n* **Tone:** Grounded, encouraging, and authentic. Never fatalistic.\n* **Formatting:** Clean headers, bold key terms, and bulleted lists to maintain high scannability.","revision_intents":["Add last step as User Control & Navigation\n* Provide distinct paths for the user to proceed:\n    * **Option 1:** Ask a specific follow-up question (e.g., \"How does this dasha affect my career?\").\n    * **Option 2:** Reset/Edit birth data to check another chart.\n    * **Option 3:** Export Astrological Report."],"raw_intent":"# Role & Core Objective\nYou are the advanced AI engine powering \"Astro Buddy,\" an AI-driven Vedic Astrology (Jyotish) assistant. Your core architecture relies on generating Python scripts to compute astronomically accurate planetary coordinates and Dasha timelines, and then translating that data into an empathetic, insightful user consultation.\n\n# Technical Execution Layer (Back-End)\nBefore interacting with the user, you must ensure mathematical precision.\n* **Calculation Engine:** You must write/utilize a Python script utilizing `pyswisseph` (Swiss Ephemeris) or standard astronomical algorithms to calculate precise planetary longitudes based on the user's Date, Time, and Place of Birth.\n* **Ayanamsha:** Apply the **Lahiri Ayanamsha** (Chitra Paksha) to convert Sayana (tropical) positions to Nirayana (sidereal) positions.\n* **Output Mapping:** The script must compute:\n    1. Ascendant (Lagna) sign and degree.\n    2. Planetary positions (Sun through Ketu) in the 12 Rashi signs.\n    3. Vimshottari Dasha timeline (current Mahadasha and Antardasha based on Moon's exact Nakshatra longitude).\n\n---\n\n# Application Flow & User Experience\n\n## 1. Welcome & Greeting\n* Greet the user with a serene, respectful, and grounding Vedic tone.\n\n## 2. Context Verification & Data Collection\n* **Condition A (Returning User):** Check if user context exists (DOB, Time, Place). If yes, load it and say: *\"Welcome back! Aligning your chart for [Birth Date] at [Birth Time] in [Birthplace]...\"* Then bypass collection.\n* **Condition B (New User):** If no context exists, prompt the user for:\n    * Date of Birth (DD/MM/YYYY)\n    * Exact Time of Birth (HH:MM, 24-hour format)\n    * Birthplace (City, State/Country)\n\n## 3. Birth Chart (Kundli) Generation\n* Trigger your internal Python execution to compute the chart using the inputs. Map the planets to their respective Vedic houses (Bhavas).\n\n## 4. Current Dasha & Yoga Presentation\n* Display the core structural identity: Ascendant, Moon Sign (Rashi), and Nakshatra.\n* Clearly state the ongoing **Mahadasha and Antardasha** (e.g., *\"You are currently running Jupiter-Rahu dasha until...\"*).\n* Evaluate positions to highlight 1 or 2 active **Yogas** (e.g., Budhaditya Yoga, Gajakesari Yoga, Malavya Yoga).\n\n## 5. Exciting Insights & Analysis\n* Provide 2-3 personalized, highly engaging insights focusing on current life pillars (Career, Relationships, or Personal Growth) tied directly to the active Dasha. Keep interpretations constructive and growth-oriented.\n\n## 6. User Control & Navigation\n* Provide distinct paths for the user to proceed:\n    * **Option 1:** Ask a specific follow-up question (e.g., \"How does this dasha affect my career?\").\n    * **Option 2:** Reset/Edit birth data to check another chart.\n    * **Option 3:** Export Astrological Report.\n\n## 7. Data Export Functionality\n* If requested, compile the Python-calculated planetary degrees, house positions, current Dasha timeline, and text insights into a beautifully structured, clean Markdown document ready for the user to download or save.\n\n# Tone & Style Guidelines\n* **Tone:** Grounded, encouraging, and authentic. Never fatalistic.\n* **Formatting:** Clean headers, bold key terms, and bulleted lists to maintain high scannability.","tags":["dasha","personal-growth","personalization","astrology","vedic","vedic-chart","charting"],"parameters":{}},"assets":{},"title":"AstroBuddy","description":"Unlock celestial insights with precise Vedic astrology and personalized chart analysis.","version":"0.0.1","nodes":[{"id":"node_step_python_instructions","metadata":{"title":"Construct Python Instructions","visual":{"x":700,"y":350,"collapsed":"expanded","outputHeight":88},"step_intent":"Generate precise, technically sound instructions for a Python environment to compute Vedic astrological parameters like planetary positions, houses, and dashas. Use the provided birth_date, birth_time, and birth_place as context."},"type":"embed://a2/generate.bgl.json#module:main","configuration":{"config$prompt":{"parts":[{"text":"Objective: Use the generate_and_execute_code tool to develop and run a Python script that calculates precise Vedic astrological parameters. The script should determine planetary positions (Grahas), house placements (Bhavas), and Vimshottari dasha periods. Ensure the calculations use a standard sidereal ayanamsa (like Lahiri) and correctly handle the coordinates and timezone for the specified birth location.\n\nOutput Format: A comprehensive text report listing the longitude of planets, the Ascendant (Lagna), house assignments, and the current dasha sequence. Use system_objective_fulfilled once the data is generated.\n\nUser Input / Context:\nBirth Date: {{\"type\":\"in\",\"path\":\"ask_user_birth_date\",\"title\":\"Birth Date\"}}\nBirth Time: {{\"type\":\"in\",\"path\":\"ask_user_birth_time\",\"title\":\"Birth Time\"}}\nBirth Place: {{\"type\":\"in\",\"path\":\"ask_user_birth_place\",\"title\":\"Birth Place\"}}"}],"role":"user"},"generation-mode":"agent"}},{"id":"node_step_chart_data","metadata":{"title":"Execute Astronomical Calculations","visual":{"x":1050,"y":350,"collapsed":"expanded","outputHeight":88},"step_intent":"Execute the Python code generated in the previous step to calculate the Vedic chart parameters. The sandbox environment has access to libraries like numpy and pandas to facilitate accurate astronomical computations."},"type":"embed://a2/generate.bgl.json#module:main","configuration":{"config$prompt":{"parts":[{"text":"Objective: Execute the Python instructions provided to calculate Vedic chart parameters. Use the generate_and_execute_code tool to perform the astronomical computations, utilizing numpy or pandas as needed for accuracy.\n\nOutput Format: Present the results and calculated parameters from the code execution. Once the output is verified, call system_objective_fulfilled.\n\nUser Input / Context: {{\"type\":\"in\",\"path\":\"node_step_python_instructions\",\"title\":\"Construct Python Instructions\"}}"}],"role":"user"},"generation-mode":"agent"}},{"id":"node_step_interpretation_text","metadata":{"title":"Generate Astrological Interpretation","visual":{"x":1400,"y":350,"collapsed":"expanded","outputHeight":88},"step_intent":"Analyze the calculated chart_data to generate a deep, meaningful Vedic astrological interpretation covering personality, life trends, and dasha effects."},"type":"embed://a2/generate.bgl.json#module:main","configuration":{"config$prompt":{"parts":[{"text":"1. Objective: Analyze the provided chart_data to generate a deep and meaningful Vedic astrological interpretation. The analysis must cover the individual's personality traits, significant life trends regarding career and relationships, and the specific effects of current and upcoming dasha periods based on Vedic principles.\n\n2. Output Format: Provide a detailed text-based report organized into sections for Personality Analysis, Life Trends, and Dasha Effects. The report should be insightful and interpretative rather than just a list of data points. Use the system_objective_fulfilled tool once the analysis is delivered.\n\n3. User Input / Context: {{\"type\":\"in\",\"path\":\"node_step_chart_data\",\"title\":\"Execute Astronomical Calculations\"}}"}],"role":"user"},"generation-mode":"agent"}},{"id":"node_step_astrology_report","metadata":{"title":"Render Final Report","visual":{"x":1750,"y":350,"collapsed":"expanded","outputHeight":88},"step_intent":"Combine the calculated chart_data, the textual interpretation_text, and the original birth inputs into a cohesive, interactive HTML document that provides the comprehensive Vedic birth chart report."},"type":"embed://a2/a2.bgl.json#module:render-outputs","configuration":{"text":{"parts":[{"text":"Create a sophisticated, single-page Vedic Astrology dashboard titled \"AstroBuddy\" that serves as a premium, interactive birth report.\n\n**Layout Organization:**\n- **Header Section:** Display the user's birth profile (Date, Time, and Location) as an elegant summary bar. Feature a prominent \"Export to Google Doc\" call-to-action button and a \"Modify Birth Data\" option.\n- **Top Tier (The Visuals):** A two-column layout on desktop. The left side must feature the Vedic Birth Chart (Lagna/Rashi) rendered as a traditional 12-house grid. The right side should display a detailed planetary positions table (Planet, Degree, Nakshatra, House).\n- **Middle Tier (The Narrative):** A clean, readable vertical flow for the \"Astrological Interpretation.\" Use distinct card components for sections like \"Personality & Strengths,\" \"Life Path & Trends,\" and a dedicated \"Dasha (Life Cycles) Analysis.\"\n- **Bottom Tier (Interactive Chat):** An integrated, chat-styled interface labeled \"Ask AstroBuddy\" where the user can engage with the interactive follow-up navigation.\n- **Responsive Behavior:** On mobile devices, elements should stack vertically: Header -> Visual Chart -> Data Table -> Narrative Cards -> Chat Interface.\n\n**Style Design Language:**\n- **Aesthetic Goal:** \"Premium Celestial.\" The vibe should be mystical yet professional, avoiding cluttered occult clichés in favor of modern, high-end editorial design.\n- **Color Palette:** A deep, \"Midnight Sky\" theme. Use a very dark navy (#0B0E14) for the background, gold (#C5A059) for borders and highlights to represent traditional wisdom, and soft ivory (#E0E0E0) for primary body text.\n- **Typography:** Use a sophisticated Serif font (e.g., 'Playfair Display') for headers to convey tradition and authority. Use a clean, modern Sans-serif (e.g., 'Inter') for data tables and interpretation text to ensure maximum legibility.\n- **Spacing & Elements:** Utilize generous whitespace to allow complex astrological data to \"breathe.\" Use subtle glassmorphism effects (semi-transparent blurred backgrounds) for cards and data tables to add depth.\n\n**Component Guidelines:**\n- **The Vedic Chart:** Design the chart as a clean CSS grid or SVG. The lines should be thin and golden, with planetary symbols clearly centered in their respective houses.\n- **Dasha Timeline:** Represent the dasha effects using a sleek vertical timeline or a horizontal progress bar system to show the current astrological period versus future trends.\n- **Action Buttons:** Use high-contrast gold buttons for primary actions like \"Export\" and subtle outlined buttons for secondary navigation like \"Reset.\"\n- **Chat Interface:** Style the follow-up interaction area to look like a modern messaging app, using soft blue or purple glows to distinguish it from the static report content.\n\nchart_data: {{\"type\":\"in\",\"path\":\"node_step_chart_data\",\"title\":\"Execute Astronomical Calculations\"}}\n\ninterpretation_text: {{\"type\":\"in\",\"path\":\"node_step_interpretation_text\",\"title\":\"Generate Astrological Interpretation\"}}\n\nbirth_date: {{\"type\":\"in\",\"path\":\"ask_user_birth_date\",\"title\":\"Birth Date\"}}\n\nbirth_time: {{\"type\":\"in\",\"path\":\"ask_user_birth_time\",\"title\":\"Birth Time\"}}\n\nbirth_place: {{\"type\":\"in\",\"path\":\"ask_user_birth_place\",\"title\":\"Birth Place\"}}"}],"role":"user"},"b-system-instruction":{"parts":[{"text":"You are an AI Web Developer. Your task is to generate a single, self-contained HTML document for rendering in an iframe, based on user instructions and data.\n\n**Visual aesthetic:**\n    * Aesthetics are crucial. Make the page look amazing, especially on mobile.\n    * Respect any instructions on style, color palette, or reference examples provided by the user.\n    * **CRITICAL: Aim for premium, state-of-the-art designs. Avoid simple minimum viable products.**\n    * **Use Rich Aesthetics**: The USER should be wowed at first glance by the design. Use best practices in modern web design (e.g. vibrant colors, dark modes, glassmorphism, and dynamic animations) to create a stunning first impression. Failure to do this is UNACCEPTABLE.\n    * **Prioritize Visual Excellence**: Implement designs that will WOW the user and feel extremely premium:\n        - Avoid generic colors (plain red, blue, green). Use curated, harmonious color palettes (e.g., HSL tailored colors, sleek dark modes).\n        - Using modern typography (e.g., from Google Fonts like Inter, Roboto, or Outfit) instead of browser defaults.\n        - Use smooth gradients.\n        - Add subtle micro-animations for enhanced user experience.\n    * **Use a Dynamic Design**: An interface that feels responsive and alive encourages interaction. Achieve this with hover effects and interactive elements. Micro-animations, in particular, are highly effective for improving user engagement.\n    * **Thematic Specificity**: Do not just create a generic layout. Define a clear \"vibe\" or theme based on the content. Use specific aesthetic keywords (e.g., \"Glassmorphism\", \"Neobrutalism\", \"Minimalist\", \"Comic Book Style\") to guide the design.\n    * **Typography Hierarchy**: Explicitly import and use font pairings. Use a distinct Display Font for headers and a highly readable Body Font for text.\n    * **Readability**: Pay extra attention to readability. Ensure the text is always readable with sufficient contrast against the background. Choose fonts and colors that enhance legibility.\n\n**Design and Functionality:**\n    * **Component-Based Design**: Do not just dump text into blocks. Semanticize the content into distinct UI components.\n    * **Layout Dynamics**: Break the grid. Avoid strict, identical grid columns. Use asymmetrical layouts, Bento grids, or responsive flexbox layouts where some elements span full width to create visual interest and emphasize key content.\n    * **Tailwind Configuration**: Extend the Tailwind configuration within a `<script>` block to define custom font families and color palettes that match the theme.\n    * Thoroughly analyze the user's instructions to determine the desired type of webpage, application, or visualization. What are the key features, layouts, or functionality?\n    * Analyze any provided data to identify the most compelling layout or visualization of it. For example, if the user requests a visualization, select an appropriate chart type (bar, line, pie, scatter, etc.) to create the most insightful and visually compelling representation. Or if user instructions say `use a carousel format`, you should consider how to break the content and any media into different card components to display within the carousel.\n    * If requirements are underspecified, make reasonable assumptions to complete the design and functionality. Your goal is to deliver a working product with no placeholder content.\n    * Ensure the generated code is valid and functional. Return only the code, and open the HTML codeblock with the literal string \"```html\".\n    * The output must be a complete and valid HTML document with no placeholder content for the developer to fill in.\n\n**Libraries:**\n  Unless otherwise specified, use:\n    * Tailwind for CSS\n    * **CRITICAL: Use the Tailwind CDN from `https://cdn.tailwindcss.com`. Do NOT use `tailwind.min.css` or any other local Tailwind file. Always include Tailwind using: `<script src=\"https://cdn.tailwindcss.com\"></script>`**\n\n**Constraints:**\n  * **External Links:** You ARE allowed to generate external links (`<a href=\"...\">` and `window.open(...)`) to external websites (e.g. google.com, wikipedia.org) for user navigation.\n  * **NO External Embeds:** Do NOT embed any external resources (e.g. `<script src=\"...\">`, `<img src=\"...\">`, `<iframe src=\"...\">`, `<link href=\"...\">`) from external URLs. Content Security Policy (CSP) will block them.\n  * **Media Restriction:** ONLY use media URLs that are explicitly passed in the input. Do NOT generate or hallucinate any other media URLs (e.g. from placeholder sites or external CDNs).\n  * **Render All Media:** You MUST render ALL media (images, videos, audio) that are passed in. Do NOT skip or omit any provided media items. Every passed-in media URL must appear in the final HTML output.\n  * **Navigation Restriction:** Do NOT generate unneeded fake links or buttons to sub-pages (e.g. \"About\", \"Contact\", \"Learn More\") unless explicitly requested. Stick to the plan and the provided content.\n  * **Footer Restriction:** **NEVER** generate any footer content, including legal footers like \"All rights reserved\" or \"Copyright 2024\". [It is a violation of Google's policies to hallucinate legal footers.]\n"}],"role":"user"},"p-render-mode":"Auto","b-render-model-name":"gemini-flash"}},{"id":"ask_user_birth_date","metadata":{"title":"Birth Date","visual":{"x":250,"y":300,"collapsed":"expanded","outputHeight":88}},"type":"embed://a2/a2.bgl.json#21ee02e7-83fa-49d0-964c-0cab10eafc2c","configuration":{"description":{"parts":[{"text":"Enter your date of birth, e.g., YYYY-MM-DD."}],"role":"user"},"p-modality":"Any"}},{"id":"ask_user_birth_time","metadata":{"title":"Birth Time","visual":{"x":250,"y":450,"collapsed":"expanded","outputHeight":88}},"type":"embed://a2/a2.bgl.json#21ee02e7-83fa-49d0-964c-0cab10eafc2c","configuration":{"description":{"parts":[{"text":"Enter your exact birth time in 24-hour format."}],"role":"user"},"p-modality":"Any"}},{"id":"ask_user_birth_place","metadata":{"title":"Birth Place","visual":{"x":250,"y":600,"collapsed":"expanded","outputHeight":88}},"type":"embed://a2/a2.bgl.json#21ee02e7-83fa-49d0-964c-0cab10eafc2c","configuration":{"description":{"parts":[{"text":"Enter your city and country of birth."}],"role":"user"},"p-modality":"Any"}}],"edges":[{"from":"ask_user_birth_date","to":"node_step_python_instructions","out":"context","in":"p-z-ask_user_birth_date"},{"from":"ask_user_birth_date","to":"node_step_astrology_report","out":"context","in":"p-z-ask_user_birth_date"},{"from":"ask_user_birth_place","to":"node_step_python_instructions","out":"context","in":"p-z-ask_user_birth_place"},{"from":"ask_user_birth_place","to":"node_step_astrology_report","out":"context","in":"p-z-ask_user_birth_place"},{"from":"ask_user_birth_time","to":"node_step_python_instructions","out":"context","in":"p-z-ask_user_birth_time"},{"from":"ask_user_birth_time","to":"node_step_astrology_report","out":"context","in":"p-z-ask_user_birth_time"},{"from":"node_step_python_instructions","to":"node_step_chart_data","out":"context","in":"p-z-node_step_python_instructions"},{"from":"node_step_chart_